A Doonside shopkeeper in KwaZulu-Natal has been shot dead while opening his store on Main Road at about 6.45am this morning, the South Coast Sun reports.While details are still sketchy, it is believed four armed men stormed into the First Pride Mini Superette shop while the store owner was opening for the day, and he was shot dead. It is not known whether anything was taken from the store.The men were apparently seen fleeing the scene by a passersby. Caxton News ServiceRead original story on southcoastsun.co.za